# **Deep Analysis: Existing Contract vs. v5.3 Group Mechanics**

## **Part 1: Current Contract Architecture Analysis**

Based on the documents provided, I need to first understand what exists, then propose specific integration points for the new group mechanics.

### **Current System (from documents):**

```
Existing Features:
â”œâ”€â”€ Riddle NFTs with randomized parameters
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ Max Mint Rate: 10-1,000 copies
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ Prize Pool: 100K-10M RDLN
â”‚   â””â”€â”€ Winner Slots: 1-100 winners
â”‚
â”œâ”€â”€ RDLN Token (ERC-20 on Polygon)
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ 1B total supply
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ Deflationary burn mechanics
â”‚   â””â”€â”€ Multi-signature treasury
â”‚
â”œâ”€â”€ Burn Protocol (Fibonacci sequence)
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ Failed attempts: 1,1,2,3,5,8,13... RDLN
â”‚   â””â”€â”€ 50% burn, 25% Grand Prize, 25% Dev
â”‚
â”œâ”€â”€ Question Submission System
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ Progressive cost (1,2,3...N RDLN per question)
â”‚   â””â”€â”€ Multi-validator approval
â”‚
â””â”€â”€ RON Reputation (Soul-bound tokens)
    â”œâ”€â”€ Earned through solving
    â”œâ”€â”€ Gates oracle validation tiers
    â””â”€â”€ Non-transferable
```

